%2Fa%3E.%20Now%2C%20with%20all%20the%20additional%20baby%20stuff%2C%20the%20place%20resembled%20a%20storage%20unit.%20I%20knew%20it%20was%20time%20to%20pare%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20ever%20since%20becoming%20a%20mom%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhouse-fire-decluttering-lesson-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edecluttering%20has%20been%20difficult%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20one%20thing%2C%20there's%20the%20issue%20of%20time.%20With%20young%20kids%2C%20finding%20an%20hour%20to%20sit%20down%20and%20sort%20through%20a%20drawer%20is%20practically%20impossible.%20When%20I%20last%20tried%20to%20declutter%20my%20closet%2C%20my%20daughters%20turned%20the%20cleaning%20session%20into%20a%20princess%20costume%20playdate%2C%20using%20my%20dresses%20to%20put%20on%20a%20fashion%20show.%20It%20was%20very%20cute%20%E2%80%94%20though%20unproductive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20also%20difficult%20because%2C%20since%20I%20started%20having%20kids%2C%20I've%20become%20extremely%20sentimental.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESure%2C%20I%20can%20open%20a%20closet%20and%20find%20a%20few%20old%20toys%20we%20don't%20need%2C%20but%20if%20I%20happen%20to%20uncover%20one%20of%20my%20kids'%20former%20favorite%20stuffed%20animals%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F3-things-parents-can-do-with-kids-school-art-from-professional-declutterer-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ea%20piece%20of%20preschool%20art%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20says%20%26quot%3BMommy%2C%26quot%3B%20I'll%20turn%20into%20emotional%20goo.%20Not%20only%20will%20I%20insist%20this%20item%20should%20never%20leave%20the%20house%2C%20but%20suddenly%2C%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20give%20anything%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a37bc47b-1ea2-4c6d-a222-73431e6ff839%5C%22%3EI%20don't%20schedule%20time%20to%20purge%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20selecting%20just%20one%20thing%20to%20trash%20or%20donate%20each%20day%20works%20for%20me.%20I%20don't%20need%20to%20schedule%20time%20to%20do%20it%2C%20and%20I%20don't%20have%20an%20opportunity%20to%20get%20too%20emotional.%20I%20just%20pick%20one%20thing%20from%20anywhere%20in%20the%20house%2C%20put%20it%20in%20the%20trash%20or%20the%20%26quot%3Bdonation%20bag%26quot%3B%20in%20my%20trunk%2C%20and%20I'm%20done.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.lakehuronwellnessconsulting.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENatalie%20Nugent%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20licensed%20clinical%20psychologist%20based%20in%20Huron%20County%2C%20MI%2C%20told%20me%20that%20creating%20micro%20goals%20is%20a%20smart%20way%20to%20make%20decluttering%20feel%20doable.%20When%20one%20feels%20overwhelmed%2C%20breaking%20tasks%20down%20into%20concrete%20and%20manageable%20steps%20is%20a%20great%20strategy%2C%20according%20to%20Nugent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20adds%20that%20turning%20one%20big%20project%20into%20many%20smaller%20tasks%20can%20help%20a%20person%20feel%20comfortable%20enough%20to%20get%20started%2C%20which%20can%20sometimes%20be%20the%20hardest%2C%20most%20important%20part.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20while%20I've%20broken%20down%20my%20decluttering%20mission%20into%20what%20might%20seem%20like%20embarrassingly%20small%20daily%20goals%2C%20it's%20worked%20for%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELittle%20by%20little%20over%20the%20past%20year%2C%20this%20method%20has%20helped%20me%20get%20rid%20of%20hundreds%20of%20items%2C%20all%20while%20teaching%20me%20that%20decluttering%20doesn't%20have%20to%20be%20overwhelming%20or%20time-consuming.%20Sometimes%20it%20just%20takes%20patience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a6f502b7-1263-4339-b11d-7c4e86db04e4%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMy%20method%20is%20slow%20and%20steady%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20one%20downside%20to%20my%20method%20is%20that%20progress%20is%2C%20I'll%20admit%2C%20incredibly%20slow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20remember%20one%20day%2C%20a%20couple%20of%20months%20into%20my%20micro-de-junk%2C%20I%20stepped%20on%20a%20miniature%20plastic%20tiger%20and%20yelled%20a%20profanity%20I%20hoped%20my%20kids%20wouldn't%20repeat.%20I%20looked%20around%20my%20messy%20living%20room%2C%20in%20pain%20and%20frustrated.%20I'd%20already%20taken%20two%20big%20bags%20of%20stuff%20to%20Goodwill%2C%20and%20still%2C%20the%20bookshelf%20was%20full%20of%20tchotchkes%2C%20toys%20littered%20the%20floor%2C%20and%20sweaters%20and%20shoes%20blocked%20my%20path%20to%20the%20front%20door.%20How%20did%20I%20still%20have%20so%20much%20stuff%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theexpertbeginner.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EShannon%20Leyko%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20declutterer%20and%20host%20of%20Paring%20Down%20Podcast%2C%20said%20she's%20not%20surprised%20by%20my%20exasperation.%20She%20explained%20that%2C%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20decluttering%2C%20people%20want%20to%20see%20their%20progress.%20After%20a%20long%20day%20of%20cleaning%20and%20organizing%2C%20seeing%20a%20big%20%26quot%3Bto-go%26quot%3B%20pile%20gives%20a%20person%20a%20boost%20of%20endorphins%20and%20encouragement%20to%20keep%20going.%20Visual%20progress%2C%20she%20says%2C%20feels%20good.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20my%20small-scale%20clean%20out%2C%20though%2C%20I%20don't%20get%20that%20big%20payoff%20at%20the%20end%20of%20a%20long%20day%20of%20decluttering.%20It%20takes%20a%20while%20to%20see%20a%20difference.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221920%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Kids%20playroom%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68a5ef8b194a2d49b8aedb6c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author's%20play%20room%20before%20(left)%20and%20after%20(right)%20decluttering.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ELeyko%20says%20that%20if%20one-a-day%20decluttering%20is%20too%20slow%2C%20there%20are%20other%20mini%20cleaning%20goals%20that%20produce%20faster%20results.%20She%20recommends%20setting%20an%20alarm%20to%20declutter%20for%20just%20five%20minutes%20a%20day%20and%20mentions%20a%2030-day%20challenge%20where%20people%20declutter%20one%20thing%20on%20the%20first%20day%2C%20two%20things%20on%20the%20second%2C%20and%20so%20on%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3Bat%20the%20end%20of%20the%20challenge%2C%20they've%20decluttered%20465%20items%20in%20one%20month%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELeyko%20adds%20that%20different%20people%20work%20at%20different%20paces%2C%20but%20progress%20is%20still%20progress.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c9f15730-f8e4-4428-b965-baf72bb19a42%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt%20made%20me%20more%20thoughtful%20about%20consumption%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20I%20started%20this%20micro-dejunk%2C%20I%20was%20bad%20about%20overbuying.%20If%20I%20went%20to%20the%20store%20with%20my%20daughter%20and%20she%20found%20a%20cute%20little%20%242%20toy%20at%20the%20checkout%20stand%2C%20I'd%20have%20a%20hard%20time%20saying%20%26quot%3BNo.%26quot%3B%20Or%20if%20I%20found%20something%2C%20like%20a%20throw%20blanket%20or%20reusable%20water%20bottle%2C%20that%20I%20didn't%20necessarily%20need%20but%20was%20on%20sale%2C%20I'd%20feel%20inclined%20to%20buy%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Leyko%20warns%20that%20if%20a%20person%20only%20declutters%20one%20thing%20a%20day%2C%20they%20should%20be%20careful%20about%20how%20much%20they%20bring%20in.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20declutter%20seven%20things%20in%20one%20week%2C%20but%20then%20buy%20two%20shirts%2C%20one%20candle%2C%20one%20new%20beach%20towel%2C%20and%20three%20books%20from%20Target%2C%20then%20you've%20undone%20all%20your%20work%20for%20that%20week%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20realization%20made%20me%20more%20mindful%20of%20what%20I%20buy.%20I've%20learned%20to%20tell%20myself%20that%20just%20because%20something%20is%20inexpensive%20doesn't%20mean%20I%20should%20take%20it%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22798621c1-fdd2-42ad-a945-53a185f60a47%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELess%20stuff%2C%20less%20stress%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20nearly%20a%20year%20into%20my%20de-junk%2C%20I'm%20noticing%20a%20real%20difference%20in%20my%20home.%20My%20counters%20seem%20bigger%2C%20drawers%20close%20more%20easily%2C%20and%20toy%20bins%20aren't%20overflowing.%20Overall%2C%20it%20feels%20like%20I%20have%20more%20room%20to%20move%20and%20more%20space%20to%20breathe.%20When%20I%20look%20around%20the%20living%20room%2C%20I%20don't%20feel%20so%20stressed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'll%20be%20the%20first%20to%20admit%20that%20my%20micro-cleaning%20hasn't%20transformed%20my%20home%20from%20a%20toy-tornado%20zone%20into%20a%20minimalist%20dream%20space.%20Tchotchkis%20didn't%20completely%20disappear%2C%20and%20I%20still%20step%20on%20pointy%20plastic%20toys%20every%20so%20often.%20But%20my%20house%20feels%20better%3A%20A%20little%20more%20orderly%2C%20a%20little%20more%20tidy.%20And%20I%20feel%20good%20in%20my%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20worth%20the%20wait.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparent-decluttering-tips-overwhelmed-stuff-2025-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1755959581000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68a5daada17a8c5b405326c6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparent-decluttering-tips-overwhelmed-stuff-2025-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22I%20made%20a%20decision%20to%20get%20rid%20of%20one%20thing%20every%20day.%20It's%20a%20slow%20process%20but%20I'm%20seeing%20the%20benefits%20of%20decluttering.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Jillian%20Pretzel)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparent-decluttering-tips-overwhelmed-stuff-2025-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Emmett%20Till%20lynching%20records%20unveil%20government%20response%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1755958287