t%20price%2C%20%24575%2C%20didn't%20cover%20the%20organization's%20cost%20per%20attendee%2C%20which%20sat%20at%20about%20%24749%20in%202023.%20This%20year%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-spent-7000-go-to-burning-man-cost-would-do-it-again-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBurning%20Man%20tickets%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20priced%20on%20a%20transparent%20sliding%20scale%20from%20%26quot%3Bgive%20a%20gift%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20any%20ticket%20priced%20above%20%24750%20%E2%80%94%20to%20%26quot%3Breceive%20a%20gift%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20the%20limited%20number%20of%20tickets%20priced%20below%20%24750.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoodell%20said%20Burning%20Man's%20%26quot%3Bfinancial%20outlook%20is%20much%20stronger%20than%20where%20we%20were%20a%20year%20ago%2C%26quot%3B%20when%20it%20operated%20at%20a%20financial%20loss%20in%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20tickets%20for%20this%20year's%20festival%2C%20which%20runs%20from%20August%2024%20to%20September%201%2C%20have%20not%20sold%20out%20as%20they%20did%20each%20year%20from%202011%20to%202023%2C%20less%20those%20when%20the%20event%20was%20called%20off%20due%20to%20the%20pandemic.%20At%20its%20peak%2C%20in%202019%2C%20Burning%20Man%20hosted%2078%2C850%20attendees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20after%20higher-priced%20ticket%20sales%20did%20not%20meet%20expectations%2C%20the%20nonprofit%20raised%20its%20fundraising%20goal%20from%20%2410%20million%20at%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20year%20to%20%2420%20million%20by%20November%20to%20address%20a%20shortfall.%20Thanks%20to%2010%25%20staff%20cuts%20and%20a%20surge%20in%20donations%2C%20it%20squeaked%20through.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202023%2C%20the%20most%20recent%20year%20for%20which%20data%20is%20available%2C%20the%20organization's%20expenses%20totaled%20%2463.6%20million%2C%20more%20than%20double%20what%20they%20were%20a%20decade%20prior%2C%20according%20to%20financial%20filings.%20Those%20expenses%20cover%20staff%20and%20year-round%20activities%2C%20